Ingredients.1: 1 (30 ounce) package frozen bite-size potato nuggets (such as Tater Tots®)

Ingredients.6: 1 tablespoon buffalo wing sauce, or more to taste

Ingredients.7: 1 pinch cayenne pepper, or to taste

Ingredients.8: 1 tablespoon chopped fresh cilantro, or to taste

Directions.1: Heat air fryer to 370 degrees F (190 degrees C) for 2 minutes.

Directions.2: Add potato nuggets and cook until all pieces are cooked and crispy, shaking basket frequently, about 12 minutes. You may need to cook them in batches.

Directions.3: Divide potato nuggets between plates and top with even amounts of chicken, Cheddar cheese, and salsa.

Directions.4: Blend the ranch and buffalo sauce together in a bowl. Drizzle sauce over totchos. Garnish with cayenne pepper and cilantro.
